
Folder Structure

siem-lab-setup/
├─ wazuh-config/
│  ├─ ossec.conf
│  └─ rules/
│     └─ local_rules.xml
├─ dashboards/
│  └─ sample-dashboard.png
├─ docs/
│  └─ setup-guide.md
└─ README.md

Example Config

ossec.conf snippet

<ossec_config>
  <client>
    <server-ip>192.168.1.10</server-ip>
  </client>

  <alerts>
    <log_alert_level>7</log_alert_level>
    <email_alerts>yes</email_alerts>
  </alerts>

  <rules>
    <include>rules/local_rules.xml</include>
  </rules>
</ossec_config>

local_rules.xml snippet

<group name="ssh">
  <rule id="100100" level="10">
    <decoded_as>sshd</decoded_as>
    <description>Multiple SSH failed logins</description>
    <frequency>5</frequency>
    <timeframe>60</timeframe>
  </rule>
</group>


---

Professional README.md Example (for Linux Security)

# Linux Security Lab

## Overview
Advanced Linux security scripts and configurations for auditing, monitoring, and hardening Linux systems.

## Tools Used
- Bash/Shell scripts
- Linux commands (netstat, lastlog, grep, etc.)
- UFW / iptables

## Scripts
1. *user-audit.sh* – Audit users and sudo privileges
2. *log-monitor.sh* – Monitor login attempts
3. *system-hardening.sh* – Apply basic hardening
4. *backup-logs.sh* – Backup system logs

## Usage
```bash
chmod +x scripts/user-audit.sh
./scripts/user-audit.sh
